From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local-loongarch64-adaptation <local@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 11:11:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] platforms 1.1.0: map LoongArch host CPU

Reason:
platforms 1.1.0 already contains @platforms//cpu:loongarch64, but
host/extension.bzl still does not translate repository_ctx.os.arch values
for LoongArch. If a workspace uses @platforms//host to derive host
constraints on a LoongArch64 Linux machine, the generated host constraints
would omit the CPU constraint.

This patch is not strictly required by rules_rust after its own
get_host_triple() is fixed, but it completes the external platforms layer
for workspaces that rely on @platforms//host.

diff --git a/host/extension.bzl b/host/extension.bzl
index 69410cd..77d5e4b 100644
--- a/host/extension.bzl
+++ b/host/extension.bzl
@@ -17,6 +17,8 @@ def _translate_cpu(arch):
         return "mips64"
     if arch in ["riscv64"]:
         return "riscv64"
+    if arch in ["loongarch64", "loong64"]:
+        return "loongarch64"
     return None
 
 def _translate_os(os):
